license: MIT

abstract: >
  xlmtec is an open-source Python CLI framework for fine-tuning Large Language
  Models (LLMs) using state-of-the-art techniques including LoRA, QLoRA,
  instruction tuning, DPO (Direct Preference Optimization), knowledge
  distillation (vanilla and feature-based), and structured pruning.
  It provides a modular, production-ready pipeline with built-in evaluation
  metrics (ROUGE, BLEU, perplexity), hyperparameter sweeps via Optuna,
  model export to ONNX/GGUF/safetensors, batch inference, an interactive
  TUI, and a plugin system — all accessible through a single unified CLI
  command `xlmtec`.

